(1) 99-85 Cliff Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.W. corner of Frankfort Street, as seen from under the Brooklyn Bridge. The corner buildings (Nos. 99-95), in the rear of Nos. 22-18 Jacob Street, and was occupied by the Burr Printing House, prior to October 1934. Mark Twain was said to have been employed here.

February 15, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, exclusive of the corner proper.

February 15, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
